data.chText: 动物尸体；（尤指供食用的）畜体
data.enText: the dead body of an animal, especially of a large one or of one that is ready for cutting up as meat

simple_means.memory_skill: carc〔= carn〕肉 + ass →〔变成〕肉 → 尸体

tr: the dead body of an animal especially one slaughtered and dressed for food

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 carcase

value.def: A carcass is the body of a dead animal.

example.ex: A cluster of vultures crouched on the carcass of a dead buffalo...
example.tran: 一群秃鹫蹲伏在一具野牛的尸体上。

example.ex: Prepare the chicken stock using the carcases, the diced vegetables and herbs.
example.tran: 做鸡汤的用料有鸡肉、切成块的蔬菜和香料。

value.def: The carcass of a vehicle or building is its remains after most of it has decayed or been destroyed.

example.tran: 一辆生锈的拖拉机残骸

value.tran: (车辆、建筑物破损或被毁后的)骨架,残体

partsOfSpeech.dec: carc〔= carn〕肉 + ass →〔变成〕肉 → 尸体
carn 肉 + age 表行为 →〔把人〕切成肉的行为 → 大屠杀
carn 肉 + al …的 → 肉体的；肉欲的
carn 肉 + ival →〔疯狂吃〕肉的节日 → 狂欢节
carni 肉 + vor 吃 + ous …的 → 食肉类的
carr〔= carn〕肉 + ion 表物 → 腐肉
in 使… + carn 肉 + ate 使… → 使成为肉体状态 → 化身
re 重新 + incarnate 化身 → 使转世化身
